  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat the oven to 200°C fan."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add the beef mince to a mixing bowl with the panko breadcrumbs, harissa, pomegranate molasses, tomato paste and salt. Coarsely grate in the red onion. Use your hands to mix everything together until evenly combined."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Halve the pittas, then stuff each half with a portion of the meat mixture, pressing it in evenly. Brush both sides with olive oil."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Arrange the pittas meat-side down on an oiled wire rack set over a baking tray. Slide into the oven and cook for 10–15 mins until the meat is cooked through and the pittas are crisp and golden."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, use a mandolin or sharp knife to finely slice the cucumber and cabbage. Tip into a sieve, season with salt and toss well. Leave to sit for 10 mins to soften."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Finely chop the dill, stalks and all. In a bowl, mix together the soured cream, mustard, the zest of ¼ of the lemon, and as much juice as you like. Season with salt and black pepper, then stir through the drained cabbage and cucumber. Add more lemon juice to taste."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Once the arayes are cooked, plate them up with the slaw and any extra lemon wedges for squeezing."
    }
  ],
